    "summary": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Concluding that one disjunct of a logical disjunction must be false because the other disjunct is true; A or B; A, therefore not B.",
        "spans": [
          {
            "start": 104,
            "end": 130,
            "type": "em"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "description": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Affirming a Disjunct is a form of argument in which one disjunct of a disjunctive premise is affirmed as a premise, while the other disjunct is denied as a conclusion.",
