      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "To deny a disjunct and affirm the other disjunct as a conclusion is a validating form of argument in propositional logic which is called \"disjunctive syllogism\". Since these forms are similar, it is possible that one source of the fallacy is confusing Affirming a Disjunct with Disjunctive Syllogism.",
